shell scripting practical test paper question 1 write a shell script that takes a filename as input and prints the number of lines words and characters in the file additionally the script should prompt the user for a string and count the number of occurrences of that string in the file save the script as filestatssh and run it on a sample text file to verify that it works question 2 write a shell script that takes a directory name as input and recursively counts the number of files and directories inside the directory save the script as dirstatssh and run it on a sample directory to verify that it works question 3 write a shell script that takes a list of numbers as input and prints the sum of the numbers save the script as sumsh and run it on a sample list of numbers to verify that it works question 4 write a shell script that takes a filename as input and replaces all occurrences of a word with another word the script should prompt the user for the word to be replaced and the new word save the script as replacewordsh and run it on a sample text file to verify that it works question 5 write a shell script that takes a filename as input and converts all text to lowercase additionally the script should remove all punctuation marks and count the frequency of each word in the file sorted by frequency save the script as wordcountsh and run it on a sample text file to verify that it works question 6 write a shell script that takes a string as input and checks whether the string is a palindrome save the script as palindromesh and run it on a sample string to verify that it works question 7 write a shell script that takes a list of filenames as input and creates a tar archive of the files save the script as archivesh and run it on a sample list of files to verify that it works question 8 write a shell script that takes a filename as input and prints the number of times each word appears in the file sorted by frequency save the script as wordcountsh and run it on a sample text file to verify that it works
